    "name": "Global sensitivity analysis — hemolysis index to inlet boundary and material parameters",
    "description": "A Sobol variance-based global sensitivity analysis was performed over 2048 quasi-random samples spanning inlet velocity (±15%), blood viscosity (±10%), pump rotational speed (±5%), and hemolysis power-law exponent (±8%). The relative hemolysis index (RHI) was found to be most sensitive to rotational speed (first-order Sobol index S1=0.47) and inlet velocity (S1=0.31); viscosity and power-law exponent contributed S1<0.12 each. Total-order indices confirmed no dominant higher-order interactions. Results informed the uncertainty budget and validated that the acceptance criterion RHI<1 holds with 97.3% confidence across the full parameter space.",
    "method": "Sobol variance-based global sensitivity (quasi-Monte Carlo, Saltelli sampling)",
    "dominantFactors": [
      "rotational speed",
      "inlet velocity"
    ],
    "sampleSize": 2048
  },
