      "description": "Model is applicable only to the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry operating in steady-state laminar-to-transitional regimes (Re 200–4000) with Newtonian blood surrogate (hematocrit 35–45%). Applicability excludes pulsatile flow modes, non-Newtonian shear-thinning regimes, and patient-specific anatomical geometries."
