    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 credibility factors assessed at requiredLevel 5 with achievedLevel 5. Validation metric E<1 for all primary QoIs at all COU operating points. Discretization error GCI=1.4% well within MRL 5 threshold. UQ ensemble confirms 97.3% probability of satisfying RHI<1 acceptance criterion across full input uncertainty space. Sobol sensitivity analysis identifies rotational speed and inlet velocity as dominant uncertainty contributors; both characterized with NIST-traceable measurements. Model form uncertainty quantified via three-model ensemble. Software quality assurance program meets ISO 9001:2015 and FDA 21 CFR Part 11 requirements. Independent analyst reproducibility <1%. All validation activities conducted on identical geometry and fluid at COU operating conditions with negligible extrapolation distance. The totality of structured evidence supports acceptance of the CFD model for regulatory use in identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device.",
